title: [Caffe2 Bug] "NodeProto" is not defined.
body_html:
Issue description

This issue was found on both Windows (VS2015+cmake+ninja) and Linux (gcc5+cmake+ninja), with external protobuf (latest version build from source).

There's a high possibility of build failure when I call cmake --build . for the first time.

onnx_onnx_c2.proto: File not found.
onnx-operators_onnx_c2.proto: Import "onnx_onnx_c2.proto" was not found or had errors.
onnx-operators_onnx_c2.proto:64:12: "NodeProto" is not defined.

But it will continue to build and finish successfully if I call cmake --build . again.

This issue was never triggered when I switch on BUILD_CUSTOM_PROTO.
